The abducted Managing Director of the Bank of Agriculture, Alwan Ali-Hassan, on Wednesday, regained freedom from his abductors. Ali-Hassan was one of the passengers of the ill-fated Kaduna-Abuja train. He was kidnapped alongside over 100 passengers whose train was bombed by bandits. However, the attackers killed eight passengers, while scores were Kidnapped A family source told DAILY POST in Kaduna that the BOA boss was released on Wednesday after paying an undisclosed amount as ransom. Although, there was no confirmation from the government, a staff of Bank of Agric said he was released, but did not disclose the amount paid as ransom.